THE Mngomezulus used to be a happy family, but that is all in the past . . . Now they are being stalked by death!In just two weeks, the family from Zola in Soweto have lost two family members.Bheki (37) died two weeks ago on 31 May and Jabulile (61) died on 7 June at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital . . . She was struggling to deal with the loss of her son!The family are now devastated. Not only are they struggling to deal with the double tragedy, they are sitting with serious financial worries.How are they going to bury their mother, having just buried a son?Aunt Dudu Kubai said the family can&rsquo;t find peace and can&rsquo;t afford funeral costs.&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t have the money to bury her,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re worried she&rsquo;ll be given a pauper&rsquo;s funeral. &ldquo;We had a cleansing ceremony for Bheki, and now we&rsquo;re faced with another funeral.&ldquo;We&rsquo;re suffering the curse of two deaths in a row and struggling to recover. We&rsquo;re wondering who is next.&rdquo;She said they used to be a happy family.&ldquo;Now we have a dark cloud hanging over our heads,&rdquo; said the worried Dudu.